# Gradle tasks via MCP

For **all Gradle task execution and build verification** in this repository, prefer the `gradle` MCP server (`nise-nabe/gradle-tapi-mcp-server` v0.5.1) over shell `./gradlew`.

## Before running tasks

1. `gradle_connection_status` — confirm `connectedAny: true`
2. If not connected, `gradle_connect` with the repository root (or rely on `GRADLE_PROJECT_DIR` from `.cursor/mcp.json` / `.github/scripts/gradle-mcp-server.sh`)

Read `.cursor/skills/gradle-tapi-mcp/SKILL.md` for the full workflow.

## Default tools

| Goal | MCP tool |
|------|----------|
| Environment / versions | `gradle_get_build_environment` |
| Module tree | `gradle_get_project_overview` |
| Compile | `gradle_run_tasks` with `[":plugin:compileKotlin"]` |
| Lint Kotlin (when Kotlin/`.editorconfig` staged) | `gradle_run_tasks` with `["ktlintCheck"]`, `background: true` + poll — see **Before committing** |
| Tests (batch classes/methods in one call) | `gradle_run_tests` with `background: true` + poll |
| Full verify | `gradle_run_tasks` with `["build"]`, `background: true` + poll |

Use `background: true` and poll `gradle_get_build_status` for anything that may exceed ~30s (cold start, `:plugin:test`, `build`).

## Before committing

When `git diff --cached --name-only -- '*.kt' '*.kts' '.editorconfig'` is non-empty, coding agents must run `ktlintCheck` (MCP with `background: true` + poll, or `./gradlew ktlintCheck`), fix violations with `ktlintFormat` or manual edits, re-run `ktlintCheck` until clean, and only then `git commit`. Wait for any in-flight MCP build to finish or cancel it before commit-time ktlint. Omit ktlint when the staged index contains none of those paths.

## Shell fallback only when

- MCP tools time out or the server is unresponsive (poll `gradle_list_builds` / `gradle_get_build_status` first)
- `BUILD_ALREADY_RUNNING` and you cannot cancel the in-flight MCP build
- PR / CI parity requires `./gradlew build` after MCP verification passes

Do **not** run MCP `gradle_run_tests` and shell `./gradlew :plugin:test` on the same checkout concurrently.
